COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE, Petitioner, v. Mrs. Gladys BILICKE, Respondent. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE, Petitioner, v. Mrs. Nancy DE ROULET, Respondent. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE, Petitioner, v. Mrs. Gladys BILICKE, Guardian of Carl A. Bilicke, Minor, Respondent. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE, Petitioner, v. Mrs. Gladys BILICKE, Guardian of A. Constant Bilicke, Minor, Respondent. Nos. 6559-6562. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Aug. 10, 1931. G. A. Youngquist, Asst. Atty. Gen., and C. M. Charest, Gen. Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for petitioner. Claude I. Parker and Ralph W. Smith, both of Los Angeles, Cal., for respondents.

Before SAWTELLE, Circuit Judge, and ST. SURE, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Pursuant to motion of counsel for petitioner, consented to by counsel for respondents, ordered petition to review in each of above causes dismissed without prejudice to rights of any party; mandate in each cause forthwith.
